Algebra Explorer is an app that help you, well, explore algebra! It consists of five main parts which are all integrated into each other:

Symbolic calculator

Algebra Explorer r en app som hjlper dig utforska algebra! Den har fem delar som alla r integrerade med varandra:

Minirknare

Click an expression to load it into the calculator!

 This tab collects various information about the app as a whole. TODO more to come!
 Denna tabb samlar blandad vergripande information om appen. TODO mer text kommer!
This tab collects various information about the app as a whole.
Denna tabb samlar blandad vergripande information om appen.
 On the first tab you'll find the calculator, the heart of the app. Here you can enter an algebraic expression and get a result view with a simplification and/or a decimal form rewrite of the expression you entered. You will also be shown every individual substep, complete with explanations of what they entail.

If you need help with what to enter you can click the button to the left of the textfield which will open a window with examples for all kinds of expressions that Algebra Explorer knows. There's also a history section with your previous entries. Click on any expression in this window to load it into the calculator!

While you're entering an expression into the calculator you will be shown an analysis of it, in form of both a rendering and a textual description. As is always the case in Algebra Explorer, you can click the mathematical words in the description in order to be shown the definition of that word from the Glossary.
 P den frsta tabben hittar du minirknaren, som r hjrtat i appen. Hr kan du mata in ett algebraiskt uttryck och f en resultatvy med en frenkling och/eller decimalformsomskrivning av det givna uttrycket. I denna kan ocks se varje enskilt delsteg, komplett med frklaringar fr varje led.

Om du behver hjlp med att skriva in i rknaren kan du trycka p knappen till vnster om textfltet, vilket ppnar ett fnster med exempel fr alla sorters uttryck som Algebra Explorer knner till. Hr finns ocks en historik med de uttryck som du tidigare har skrivit in. Klicka p vilket uttryck som helst i detta fnster fr att ladda in det i rknaren.

Medan du skriver i rknaren kommer du ocks f se en analys av uttrycket du skrivit in, i form av bde en rendering och en beskrivning i klartext.Som alltid i Algebra Explorer s kan du klicka p de matematiska orden i beskrivningen fr att komma direkt till det ordets definition i Ordlistan.
This is a symbolic calculator, that will simplify the expression you enter and also show each substep in the process.

 On the third tab you'll find the Operations index. It has a list of all operations that Algebra Explorer knows. As the list is rather large there is a filter up top, allowing you to select which categories of operations should be shown.

Firstly you can select whether to show basic or complex operations. Basic operations are the fundamental laws of mathematics, while complex operations are made up by substeps of other basid and/or complex operations.

You can also filter by what effect the operation has: simplifying, conditionally simplifying, rephrasing, complicating, rewriting to decimal form or integrity checking.

Each operation link is marked green ( ) if you have learned the operation, yellow ( ) if you are able to, and red ( ) if you cannot (because it is a complex operation containing substep operations that you haven't learned). For more information on this, see the help section for the Lesson list tab!

Click an operation to be taken to a thorough presentation of it, which has three different sections:
Explanation:
An explanation of how the operation works and what it does.
Links:
A list of words and other operations that are relevant to this operation.
Learn:
An overview of the learning status for the operation and the lesson it belongs to. This is where you can mark the operation as learned if it has a yellow mark ( ).


Throughout the app, whenever you see a name of an operation, you can click the name to be shown its presentation.

This is the help text for the Learn section of the operation view. The other two sections are Explanation and Links, and you switch between the sections using the navigation bar at the top of the operation view.

In this section you can see the operation status in the Algebra Explorer School, as well as the status for the lesson that the operation is part of. For more information about this, see the help section for the Lesson list tab!

First you can see the operation status. There are three possible states:

If this is a complex operation with substep operations that you have not yet learned, you cannot learn this operation and it has a red mark ( ) next to its name. To find out which operations you need to learn you can navigate to the Links section to find a list of all substep operations, and look for those without a green mark ( ) next to its name.

If this is a basic operation, or a complex operation for which you have already learned all substeps, that means you are ready to learn it, and it therefore has a yellow mark ( ). You can now learn the operation by clicking the button below!

If you have already learned this operation it shows this with a green mark ( ). Should you for some reason want open the operation up for learning again, just press the button below again! If this means that other operations that depend on this operation would also be unlearned, then you will get a warning first.

The lesson status is shown in much the same way (although there is no button for the lesson here, merely a link to the lesson view):

If you haven't learned all operations in the lesson, it will have a red mark ( ). The text will say how many operations are left to learn in the lesson.

If you have learned all operations in the lesson, but not yet marked it as completed, it will have a yellow mark ( ). Follow the link to mark it as completed!

An already completed lesson will have a green mark ( ). The fact that the lesson is completed means that this operation is completed too.

Om detta r en grundlggande operation, eller en sammansatt operation som du redan lrt dig alla delsteg fr, s innebr det att du r redo att lra dig denna operation! Den har d en gul markering ( ). Du kan markera operationen som inlrd genom att trycka p knappen i lrsektionen!

Skulle du av ngon anledning vilja ppna upp operationen fr inlrning igen s r det bara att klicka p knappen n en gng fr att ta tillbaka markeringen! Om detta innebr att ytterligare operationer som r beroende av denna ocks blir avmarkerade s kommer du f en varning om detta frst.

 This tab contains the list of all lessons in the app. The lessons are a way to navigate the contents of Algebra Explorer in an organized way, sort of like a course!

Each lesson focuses on a specific theme, and is made up by a group of terms to read in the Glossary, as well as a number of operations to learn. Once all operations in a lesson are learned, the entire lesson can be completed.

Click a lesson in the list to be taken to the lesson view for that specific lesson. In the same way you can summon this view by clicking lesson names elsewhere in the app.

The colour code in a lesson link shows whether the lesson contains operations which haven't been learned ( ), if all operations are learned but the lesson isn't completed ( ), or if the lesson is completed ( ).

When you have completed all lessons you will have seen all content in Algebra Explorer, and hopefully you have become a master of Algebra in the process!

Frgkoden i en lektionslnk markerar om lektionen innehller operationer som inte r inlrda ( ), om alla operationer r inlrda men lektionen inte r avslutad ( ), eller om lektionen r avslutad ( ).

This view presents a single lesson. First you'll get a description of the lesson, explaining the theme and what the goal is.

Next you'll see a list of words from the Glossary tab, that are recommended reading for this lesson. There is no way to mark a word as read, so this is controlled purely by conscious. Click each word to see its definition!

After that comes the meat of the lesson, namely a list of operations from the Operations tab (except for the first lesson which has no operations, only words). The idea is that you study each of the operations by clicking on them to access their operation explanation view, and then switch to its operation learning view and mark it as learned.

In the final section you are shown the lesson status:

If you haven't learned all operations in the lesson, it will have a red mark ( ). The text will say how many operations are left to learn in the lesson, which will correspond to the number of operations in the previous list that haven't got a green mark ( )!

If you have learned all operations in the lesson giving all the operations a green mark ( ), but not yet marked it as completed, it will have a yellow mark ( ). Mark it as completed by clicking the button! There is little point to leaving a lesson with a yellow mark.

An already completed lesson will have a green mark ( ). The fact that the lesson is completed means that all operations above must also have green marks! If for some reason you want to open the lesson up again, click the button one more time. A lesson will also be automatically opened up if you take back a learn mark from one of its operations.

Det finns ingen strre pong med att inte avsluta en lektion nr du lrt dig alla dess operationer, s lektioner med gul markering br vara en ovanlig syn.
